        public static <iK,​iV,​oK,​oV,​iMap extends java.util.TreeMap<iK,​iV>,​oMap extends java.util.TreeMap<oK,​oV>> oMap reformat​(iMap map,

                                                                                                                                                                java.util.function.Function<iV,​oV> valueMapper,
                                                                                                                                                                java.util.Comparator<oK> replacementComparator)
        Reformats a TreeMap after the provided Functions, then returns the new map and overwrites the provided outputMapPointer with the new map. This method requires an additional comparator to be attached to the output TreeMap.
        Type Parameters:
        iK - Input map Key type.
        iV - Input map Value type.
        oK - Output map Key type.
        oV - Output map Value type.
        iMap - Type variable for the input map.
        oMap - Type variable for the output map.
        Parameters:
        map - The map to reformat.
        keyMapper - The function to apply to every key in the map.
        valueMapper - The function to apply to every value in the map.
        replacementComparator - The new comparator to be used by the map.
        Returns:
        The pointer to the new map.

        iMap - Type variable for the input map.

      • reformat

        public static <iK,​iV,​oK,​oV,​iMap extends java.util.Map<iK,​iV>,​oMap extends java.util.Map<oK,​oV>> oMap reformat​(iMap map,
                                                                                                                                                        java.util.function.Function<iK,​oK> keyMapper,
                                                                                                                                                        java.util.function.Function<iV,​oV> valueMapper)
        Reformats a map after the provided Functions, then returns the new map. This method is an overloaded version of reformat(Map, Map, Function, Function), but with null as outputMapPointer. When trying to reformat a TreeMap including its keys, please use reformat(TreeMap, Function, Function, Comparator), as that method will also set the comparator for the new map. The returned map always conforms to the given map supertype. See getMapOfParent(Map, Map).
        Type Parameters:
        iK - Input map Key type.
        iV - Input map Value type.
        oK - Output map Key type.
        oV - Output map Value type.
        iMap - Type variable for the input map.
        oMap - Type variable for the output map.
        Parameters:
        map - The map to reformat.
        keyMapper - The function to apply to every key in the map.
        valueMapper - The function to apply to every value in the map.
        Returns:
        The pointer to the new map.
        See Also:
        reformat(Map, Map, Function, Function)

      • reformat

        public static <iK,​iV,​oK,​oV,​iMap extends java.util.Map<iK,​iV>,​oMap extends java.util.Map<oK,​oV>> oMap reformat​(iMap map,
                                                                                                                                                        oMap outputMapPointer,
                                                                                                                                                        java.util.function.Function<iK,​oK> keyMapper,
                                                                                                                                                        java.util.function.Function<iV,​oV> valueMapper)
        Reformats a map after the provided Functions, then returns the new map and overwrites the provided outputMapPointer with the new map. When trying to reformat a TreeMap including its keys, consider using reformat(TreeMap, TreeMap, Function, Function, Comparator), as that method will also set the comparator for the new map. This method will try to place the old comparator in the new map, casting it to conform to Comparator<oK>. The returned map always conforms to the given map supertype. See getMapOfParent(Map, Map).
        Type Parameters:
        iK - Input map Key type.
        iV - Input map Value type.
        oK - Output map Key type.
        oV - Output map Value type.
        iMap - Type variable for the input map.
        oMap - Type variable for the output map.
        Parameters:
        map - The map to reformat.
        outputMapPointer - The output map pointer. Gets overwritten with the output map. May be null.
        keyMapper - The function to apply to every key in the map.
        valueMapper - The function to apply to every value in the map.
        Returns:
        The pointer to the new map.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ClassCastException - If the map is a TreeMap whose comparator can't be Comparator<\? super oK>.
